commit.message:
plthook: Fix a coding style issue

I forgot to install the pre-commit hooks on my new VM.  It resulted
in a pre-commit check failure on Github actions.  Let's fix it.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

Merge branch 'misc-fix'

A couple of random fixes and updates.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

test: Fix octal argument test on Archlinux (t288)

On my archlinux box, it return a different file descriptor number
and it makes the test fail.  Actually we don't care about the FD
number and only want to check the argument has correct octal numbers.

Let's change the test script to capture only arguments using -A
option for each function.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

test: Fix sched dump test failure (t166)

Since it only filters on the main function, the test result should
not have functions before it.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

uftrace: Ignore *.oy files in GIT

Those files are for python extension module to use separate compile
flags.  So they are basically object files and no need to track them.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

plthook: Check section header when DT_RELENT is missing

It seems some versions of a certain compiler don't generate
dynamic section info for the relocation entry size.  Let's
check the REL or RELA section header to get the entry size
instead of turning off the PLT hooking.

Fixed: #1903

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

test: Fix kernel dump test (t103)

I've noticed failures on the kernel test with the chrome tracing format
dump because of JSON load failure and a format error.  It seems to use
the double quote consistently in the metadata.  Also add missing TID
part in the process/thread name.

Also chrome_sort() logic should not filter out functions with "__"
because the kernel syscall routines start with it.  In the kernel test,
it needs to check the kernel function.  So let's remove it in the sort
logic and filter the functions (usually before 'main' in the user
program) by using -F filter explicitly.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

kernel: Use 'kernel' debug domain in the tracefs code

It's a part of kernel tracing so it should use the same debug domain.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

kernel: Fix saving kernel event files

During the last tracefs change, it added some mistakes on handling event
files.  It should check the return value of read_tracing_file() properly
and use get_tracing_file() when opening the subdirectory.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

kernel: Update the pattern of syscall trace functions

Sometimes it has functions like syscall_trace_enter.isra.0 depending
on the compiler optimization so it's hard to write the exact name.
Let's use a pattern to handle multiple functions with different suffix
properly.

Note that kernel internally uses glob patterns, and uftrace accepts
regex by checking list of filter functions before passing the input to
the kernel.  As it can add the name directly to the kernel here, using
the glob pattern would be easier.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

test: Fix Python SyntaxWarning on invalid escape sequence

Signed-off-by: Ameya Vikram Singh <ameya.v.singh@gmail.com>

Merge branch 'exception-guard'

Handle a corner case that an exception is thrown during initialization
of a static local variable.  In this case, a little differnet exception
handling routine in C++ is called which put uftrace in an infinite loop.

Let's handle the case separately by wrapping __cxa_guard_abort().

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

mcount: Wrap __cxa_guard_abort() for exception handling

When a static variable is defined in a function (local variable), C++
seems to add a hidden guard variable to protect it from concurrent
accesses in a multi-threaded program.  But it has an exception handling
logic with __cxa_guard_abort() which should be passed to libmcount too.

Fixed: #1902

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

Merge branch 'separate-dwarf'

Add support for the separate debug files using libdwfl.
Many distros deploy separate debug packages for system utilities and
this will improve tracing experience of such command when the debug
package is installed.  For example, you can apply dynamic tracing
with automatic arguments to the system binary like 'ls'.

Fixed: #1144

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

test: Fix some tests for separate DWARF support

Some tests need to filter on the main function only to suppress other
functions from the debug info.  Also agent tests should wait more until
the agent is actually started.  It seems checking additional debug info
takes much longer to start so it should check the socket file instead
of waiting for certain amount of time.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

build: Do not use libelf in the python extension

The python extension module is to trace python functions and it doesn't
need to deal with ELF files in general.  The only place needed is to get
the address of libmcount functions.  As it's the minimal functionality,
we can force to use the symbol-rawelf code by removing HAVE_LIBELF
definition in the PYTHON_CFLAGS.  It'd make it lighter without further
dependency.

But this requires separate handling the object files for the python
module.  Let's use a different object file suffix (.oy) to apply the
compiler flags separately.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

dwarf: Support split debuginfo using libdwfl

The libdwfl from elfutils is a dwarf frontend library and has a various
utilities to help find and use DWARF information in Linux systems.  This
includes supporting split debug files using .debug_altlink info.

Signed-off-by: Bernhard Kaindl <bernhardkaindl7@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

build: Check libdwfl as well as libdw

The libdwfl is a frontend library and distributed in libdw (it's in a
same file).  So rather than creating a new check, let's do it together.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

dwarf: Disable debuginfod from setup_child_environ()

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

dwarf: Separate setup_dwarf_info() more clearly

Do not call setup_dwarf_info() in setup_debug_info() automatically as
it's needed only for ELF/DWARF processing is needed.  Also do not export
setup_debug_info() and just reset the struct debug info for the python
dummy symbol table.  Finally it doesn't need to keep the DWARF data
after building the argument and return value information, so just call
release_dwarf_info() right after instead of waiting for the call to
release_debug_info() later.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

build: Check libdw version correctly

It needs to check the most recent version of API which is
dwarf_aggreate_size() at the moment.  It was added elfutils 0.144.

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

Merge pull request #1895 from nadongguri/nadongguri/new_arg_for_oct

Support new octal argument format ("o") for file mode (0755).
Convert the autoargs to use octal format in related functions
like chmod(2).

Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@gmail.com>

commit.message:
doc: Add documentation for a new argument format for octal values

Signed-off-by: Dongjin Na <dongjinna@gmail.com>

misc: Use octal format for filesystem functions

Some library functions deal with a file mode which is usually represented
in octal. Let's use the octal format instead of enum to avoid broken output.

Fixed: #1892
Signed-off-by: Dongjin Na <dongjinna@gmail.com>

uftrace: Support octal argument format

Enumeration values not present in uft_mode may cause unexpected output.
Adding a new argument format for octal values ("argN/o") can handle it.

Signed-off-by: Dongjin Na <dongjinna@gmail.com>
